      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "I seem to have become the default writer for point and click adventure games here at Switchaboo and for every review, I've mentioned how they tend to struggle on console due to the mechanics that the genre is built around: pointing and clicking. However, developers are beginning to learn and adapt these experiences more effectively when bringing their games to consoles and "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Lost in Play"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " seems to have jotted down some notes. "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Lost in Play"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " is less about pointing and clicking and more about moving and interacting, giving the player complete freedom to move with the left analogue stick and not have to use an awkward cursor to engage with objects and NPCs."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
